	   <tr><td colspan=2>While I agree that melees should have first shot at this, if its a guild event, or the raid leader has specified NBG, I'd love to have one of these for my cleric. Yes, that's right, cleric. <br><br>My cleric is close to getting his summoned hammer, and then a few levels later his hammer pet. Throw in the new yaulp that adds to mana regen, plus a ton to str, and attack, and I have as much mana regenning standing as sitting, and a decent shot at hitting. Add the fact that we can now bash, and that my AC is nearly 1000, fully buffed (even with defense that is slightly low, due to too much sitting and healing in my youth), and 2500hp, and I can tank/nuke/dot solo against undead, and tank/nuke against many other blue mobs.<br><br>It used to be true that clercis just sat on their butts and healed/buffed, but not any more. I actually can do some soloing now, and contribute to the melee output of a group :)<br><br>If you're not familiar with the summoned cleric hammer, it has awesome stats and ratio, and procs a 150hp dd, with a HIGH frequency. Toss on a boon of the garou, chanter haste, shammy buffs, and a nice haste item like this belt,and a cleric is a fighting machine.<br><br>Also, Note that I'm not saying that a cleric should melee in all situations. obviously, in a major mob encounter, all the clerics will be needed for the CH rotation, or healing the other raid members. However, in grind groups, and even on some raids, I don't always have to heal all that frequently. I've even been on a few hate raids, where the tanks in my group were taking no damage for several hours, while we rounded up the yard trash. Why not jump in and have some fun, instead of playing gems to while away the hours in boredom.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
